The paper discusses a game environment for training and evaluating neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of policy gradient methods and baseline models, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges of distributed infrastructure and game IO, which are relevant to computer networks (cs.GT) and multiagent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper mentions the use of visual inputs, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV).
